#Mind's Dilation (G-retest 2026-06-11): opponent's first spell each turn ->
#ingest 1 (exile their library top) -> P1 may cast the exiled card free.
#Driving here is believed right (turn-cross: P2 taps myr, shocks P1's face
#- shock CAST+RESOLVED, life 18 confirmed) but the @movedto(*|opponentstack)
#trigger NEVER FIRES: zero StackAbility from Mind's Dilation in the log.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
inplay:mind's dilation
[PLAYER2]
inplay:iron myr
hand:shock
library:eager cadet,wind drake,grizzly bears
[DO]
goto end
goto firstmain
iron myr
shock
p1
goto firstmain
choice 0
goto firstmain
choice 0
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
goto end
[ASSERT]
ENDOFTURN
[PLAYER1]
inplay:mind's dilation,wind drake
life:18
[PLAYER2]
inplay:iron myr
graveyard:shock
hand:grizzly bears
library:*
tappedinplay:1
[END]
#PARKED - NEW ROUND MAP (opponent-cast stack-trigger family, 62 data lines
#share @movedto(...|...stack)):
#  - The card's auto line PARSES (no ABILITYFACTORY error at load).
#  - Casting DOES route through putInZone(hand->stack) (MTGRules 581/758/
#    1068/1569) so the zone-change event exists.
#  - 'opponentstack' IS a recognized zone string (MTGGameZones.cpp:1709).
#  - So the break is in trigger-side matching: TrCardAddedToZone's zone
#    list vs the opponent's stack (controller-relative resolution in
#    trigger context), or the restriction{thisturn(*|opponentstack)
#    ~equalto~1} evaluation. Instrument the trigger's receiveEvent.
#  - Cheap first discriminator: does @movedto(*|mystack) fire for MY OWN
#    casts? If yes -> opponent-relative zone bug; if no -> stack zones
#    never match in movedto triggers at all (62 dead lines).
#  - Data smell (secondary): the nested newability watches
#    *[-land]|opponentGRAVEYARD but ingest EXILES - even with the outer
#    trigger fixed the may-cast leg may need from()-zone correction.
#UPDATE 2 (same sitting, post castMethod round): THREE fixes landed and the
#chain now runs MUCH deeper. (1) ENGINE: castMethod survives
#MTGCardInstance::clone() (zone moves used to rebuild from the model and
#reset it to NOT_CAST - the setX/exileRiderSuppressed precedent); (2)
#ENGINE: the four MTGRules cast sites pre-stamp castMethod BEFORE
#putInZone (the arrival event evaluates trigger restrictions before the
#Spell ctor used to stamp it - seenThisTurn(CAST_ALL) excluded the
#just-cast spell, so 'first spell this turn' counted 0); (3) DATA: the
#granted watcher now watches opponentEXILE (ingest exiles; it watched
#opponentgraveyard and fired on the SHOCK hitting the graveyard instead).
#VERIFIED NOW: trigger fires, restriction passes (count=1), ingest exiles
#the right card, the granted watcher fires ON THE DRAKE, the may prompt
#consumes choice 0, the GTA(AACastCard) goes on the stack... and resolves
#as a NO-OP. FINAL LEG MAP: MayAbility::reactToTargetClick clones the
